          {
            "Text": "[Wed 2026-04-22 03:02 PDT] You are working in a Swift iOS project: FeedReader (RSS feed reader). \n\nCreate a new file `FeedReader/FeedKnowledgeGraph.swift` that implements an autonomous knowledge graph that extracts entities from articles and builds connections between them.\n\n## Requirements\n\nFollow the EXACT same patterns as other files in this project (FeedSignalBooster.swift, FeedSentimentRadar.swift, etc.):\n- `import Foundation` only\n- Codable types for persistence\n- JSON file persistence in Documents directory\n- Notification.Name extensions\n- Full doc comments at the top\n- No external dependencies\n\n## Feature: FeedKnowledgeGraph\n\nAn autonomous knowledge graph builder that:\n\n1. **Entity Extraction**: When articles are ingested, extract entities using heuristic NLP:\n   - **People**: Capitalized word sequences (2-3 words), filtered against common non-name words\n   - **Organizations**: Words ending in Inc, Corp, Ltd, Co, or known tech/org patterns\n   - **Topics**: Frequent noun-like capitalized single words that aren't names/orgs\n   - **Locations**: Match against a built-in set of ~50 major world cities/countries\n\n2. **Knowledge Graph**: Entities are nodes. Edges connect entities that co-occur in the same article. Edge weight = number of co-occurrences. Each entity tracks which articles mentioned it.\n\n3. **Proactive Features**:\n   - `relatedArticles(for articleId:)` → finds articles sharing entities with the given one, ranked by shared entity count\n   - `entityTimeline(entity:)` → chronological list of articles mentioning an entity\n   - `emergingEntities(since:)` → entities that appeared recently and are gaining mentions\n   - `recommendations()` → proactive insights like \"Entity X appeared in 3 new articles today\", \"Articles A and B are connected through entities Y and Z\"\n   - `entityClusters()` → groups of tightly connected entities (simple greedy clustering by shared article overlap)\n   - `hotEntities(topN:)` → most mentioned entities in last 7 days\n\n4. **Types**:\n   - `KnowledgeEntity` - id, name, type (person/org/topic/location), articleIds, firstSeen, lastSeen, mentionCount\n   - `EntityEdge` - entity1Id, entity2Id, weight, articleIds  \n   - `EntityCluster` - entities, label (most prominent entity name), articleCount\n   - `KnowledgeGraphStats` - totalEntities, totalEdges, topEntities, articlesCovered\n\n5. **Auto-monitoring**: `startAutoMonitor()` / `stopAutoMonitor()` with a Timer that periodically checks for emerging entities and posts notifications.\n\n6. **Persistence**: Save/load to `feed_knowledge_graph.json` in Documents.\n\nMake the file ~500-600 lines. Include thorough doc comments. The file should compile as valid Swift with `import Foundation` only.\n\nAfter creating the file, verify it compiles:\n```\ncd C:\\Users\\onlin\\.openclaw\\workspace\\temp-builder\n```\n\nThen commit and push:\n```\ngit add FeedReader/FeedKnowledgeGraph.swift\ngit commit -m \"feat: Add FeedKnowledgeGraph - autonomous entity extraction and knowledge graph\n\nIntroduces an autonomous knowledge graph builder that extracts entities\n(people, organizations, topics, locations) from articles using heuristic\nNLP, builds a connected entity graph based on co-occurrence, and provides\nproactive features:\n\n- Entity extraction from article titles and bodies\n- Related article discovery through shared entities\n- Entity timeline tracking across feeds\n- Emerging entity detection for trending awareness\n- Entity clustering for topic constellation mapping\n- Hot entity rankings and graph statistics\n- Auto-monitor mode with periodic emerging entity alerts\n- Full JSON persistence\n\nUsage:\n  let graph = FeedKnowledgeGraph()\n  graph.ingest(articleId: \\\"a1\\\", title: \\\"...\\\", body: \\\"...\\\", date: Date())\n  let related = graph.relatedArticles(for: \\\"a1\\\")\n  let hot = graph.hotEntities(topN: 10)\n  let recs = graph.recommendations()\"\ngit push origin HEAD:main\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Push directly to main. Do NOT create a PR. Do NOT create a feature branch."
          }
        ]
      }
